                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "Drawn samples from the parameterized negative binomial distribution,\nwhere each sample is equal to N, the number of failures that\noccurred before a total of n successes was reached."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "ndarray or scalar",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Drawn samples from the parameterized negative binomial distribution,\nwhere each sample is equal to N, the number of failures that\noccurred before a total of n successes was reached."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "out",
                "type": "field_list"
              }
            ],
            "title": "Returns",
            "type": "field_list"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Returns"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The probability mass function of the negative binomial distribution is"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "P(N;n,p) = \\frac{\\Gamma(N+n)}{N!\\Gamma(n)}p^{n}(1-p)^{N},"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "where "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the number of successes, "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "p"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the\nprobability of success, "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "N+n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the number of trials, and\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\Gamma"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the gamma function. When "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is an integer,\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\frac{\\Gamma(N+n)}{N!\\Gamma(n)} = \\binom{N+n-1}{N}"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", which is\nthe more common form of this term in the pmf. The negative\nbinomial distribution gives the probability of N failures given n\nsuccesses, with a success on the last trial."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "If one throws a die repeatedly until the third time a \"1\" appears,\nthen the probability distribution of the number of non-\"1\"s that\nappear before the third \"1\" is a negative binomial distribution."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Because this method internally calls "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "Generator.poisson"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " with an\nintermediate random value, a ValueError is raised when the choice of\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "p"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " would result in the mean + 10 sigma of the sampled\nintermediate distribution exceeding the max acceptable value of the\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "Generator.poisson"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " method. This happens when "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "p"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is too low\n(a lot of failures happen for every success) and "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is too big (\na lot of successes are allowed).\nTherefore, the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "p"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " values must satisfy the constraint:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "formulas": [
              "n\\frac{1-p}{p}+10n\\sqrt{n}\\frac{1-p}{p}<2^{63}-1-10\\sqrt{2^{63}-1},"
            ],
            "type": "math_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Where the left side of the equation is the derived mean + 10 sigma of\na sample from the gamma distribution internally used as the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "lam"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "\nparameter of a poisson sample, and the right side of the equation is\nthe constraint for maximum value of "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "lam"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " in "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "Generator.poisson"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "1\n\nWeisstein, Eric W. \"Negative Binomial Distribution.\" From\nMathWorld--A Wolfram Web Resource.\nhttps://mathworld.wolfram.com/NegativeBinomialDistribution.html",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "2\n\nWikipedia, \"Negative binomial distribution\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Negative_binomial_distribution",
            "type": "raw_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "References"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "A real world example. A company drills wild-cat oil\nexploration wells, each with an estimated probability of\nsuccess of 0.1.  What is the probability of having one success\nfor each successive well, that is what is the probability of a\nsingle success after drilling 5 wells, after 6 wells, etc.?"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "rng = flops.random.default_rng()"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "s = rng.negative_binomial(1, 0.1, 100000)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "for i in range(1, 11): # doctest: +SKIP"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "probability = sum(s<i) / 100000."
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "print(i, \"wells drilled, probability of one success =\", probability)"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Examples"
      }
    ]
  },
